Loops (Flow Control):
- while loop
- do while loop
- for loop

i. while loop: First checks the condition and then executes

Syntax:
while(condition){

}

eg: 
int n;
int i=1; int sum =0;
while(i<=5){
  sum+=i;
  i++;
}  

ii. do while loop: First execute then check the condition

Syntax:
do{

} while(condition);

eg:
int i=10;
do{
    print("H");
    i++;
}while(i<=5);
 
           WHILE LOOP                         VS                              DO WHILE LOOP
- check the condition, then execute                      - execute then check the condition (for first time only)
- eg:                                                    - eg:
int i=10;                                                  int i=10;
while(i<=5){                                               do{
  print(i);                                                     print(i);                                                           i++;
}                                                           }while(i<5);
//Output:                                                   //Output: 10   
